metadata.name: Impalpable Realities: Isle of Dogs
metadata.description:
This is a subset of our "Impalpable Realities" collection on Foundation only. "Impalpable Realities" is a series of illustrations that tackle unseen realities, abstractions of the built environment no one could previously see. 

In this illustration (Isle of Dogs), the first out of ten upcoming drops the dichotomy between the richness of architecture and the poor community it is insert is visualized through the eyes of dogs. It is the strength of architecture and art, the built environment, against the real world.
